The fourth Eclogue, inscribed to Pollio, is very famous, and has given rise to much discussion. It deals with the birth of a child who shall restore the Golden Age, and many in consequence looked upon it as a prophecy of the birth of the Messiah, while Vergil was considered as, consciously or unconsciously, more Christian than Heathen.
